Flight delay Analysis and Prediction¶

Problem Statement:

Air travel is becoming increasingly complex with multiple variables impacting the same. The flight delay is one of such variables impacts carrier, Airport, and passenger and may result in significant commercial loss or reputation loss to all the stakeholders and thus huge cost on the economy. Thus, prediction of delay is crucial not only from viewpoint of a customer from the time management perspective and carrier for retention of customer faith but also from Airport point of view for managing the traffic more efficiently to optimize the number of arriving flights by appropriate adjustment of schedules. The contribution of weather conditions has been identified to be a very important contributor to these delays. The historical data containing scheduled departure and arrival times, date, origin, destination and also weather data is available and the data scientists can predict if the delay can happen or not using the flight data and aviation weather data for a specific flight.

Every single flight is observed as per their scheduled departure and arrival timestamps, to record the details of trips made, traffic conditions, etc. Flight details like Origin, destination, date of flight, scheduled departure and scheduled arrival timestamps etc. Weather stations data details like station id along with its linked AirportID, ground height etc. Hourly aviation weather conditions data also provided for 2 years etc. Origin, Destination details in-flight data can be mapped to the AirportID in other datasets.

The objective of this project:¶

  1. To predict the Flight that is it delayed or not by the help of Weather conditions given as weather Hourly Data and Weather Hpd Data, Station conditions given as all Station Data.

  2. To predict the Flight Analysis using ML Algorithms.

  3. Providing Business solution as per features that have highest impact on the Flight Delay.

Data Description:

  1. Weather Hourly Data: This data is provided for the period from 2004 to 2005 with the details like Origin,Destination,DBT,DewPointTemp,RelativeHumidityPercent,WindSpeed,WindDirection etc.

  2. Weather Hpd Data: Daily weather attributes like temperature, wind, humidity, etc. are available from year 2004 to 2005.

  3. All Stations Data: WeatherStationID, GroundHeight, StationHeight, BarometerHeight, Latitude, Longitude is given for every year from 2004 to 2005.

import datetime as dt
final_train7["new_date"] = final_train7["Day"].map(str)+"-"+final_train7["Month"].map(str)+"-"+final_train7["Year"].map(str)
final_train7['Scheduled_arrival']=pd.to_datetime(final_train7['ScheduledArrTime'],format='%H%M').dt.strftime('%H:%M')
final_train7["Actual_ArrivalTime"] = final_train7["new_date"] +" " + final_train7["Scheduled_arrival"]
final_train7['ActualArrivalTimeStamp']=final_train7['ActualArrivalTimeStamp'].str.replace("/","-")
final_train7['ActualArrivalTimeStamp']=pd.to_datetime(final_train7['ActualArrivalTimeStamp'])
final_train7['Actual_ArrivalTime']=pd.to_datetime(final_train7['Actual_ArrivalTime'])


final_train7['ActualArrivalTimeStamp2']=[d.date() for d in final_train7['ActualArrivalTimeStamp']]
final_train7['Actual_ArrivalTime2']=[d.date() for d in final_train7['Actual_ArrivalTime']]

Summary :¶

In this project I have used Machine Learning Algorithms to predict Flight Status: Delay or Not Delay. I have used a Ensemble Techniques and I found that this technique works the best.

Model Performance:

Random forest model and Xg Boost Both gave almost same performance, Accuracy turn out to be 76% on validation(x_test) With F1 Score as 0.51.

Conclusion : Most Important Features found: Visibility,Sky Conditons, Wind Speed, Relative Humidity,Hourly Precip.

Best F1 Scores got on Test Data as per the prediction by models:

  1. Random Forest = 0.46
  2. Xg Boost = 0.45
